Name: StarStruck
About the game: StarStruck is a fast-paced side-scrolling platformer based on the bizarre universe created by 36? for the StarStruck music video. The game features 12 weird worlds, each with a 36 second timer to complete, but don’t expect a quick and easy experience. Making it through the game will require master-level platformer play. The Story Far off in the perilous outer realm of deep space there is only one law; get... that… milk. The sweet and juicy milk is but the only thing that can save the human race. It’s raw kinetic energy has enough power to sustain our super-future societies and it is up to you, Spaceman Scott, to acquire it. The journey ahead will not be an easy one. Milk can be a treacherous and unforgiving element, and the worlds that you will find it are fraught with great peril. Indeed, some say that the milk is doomed. You will need to work quickly if you are to survive this journey.
